    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model demonstrates sufficient evidence across 12 of 13 V&V 40 factors at or above required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is considered acceptable given that the single test condition tested represents the bounding quasi-static case for the intended COU and is consistent with ASTM F1717 protocol requirements. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 and < 10% difference acceptance criteria. The overall credibility package supports an Accepted decision for the stated COU.",
